","cve_ids":[],"singular_disclosure_disabled":true,"disclosed_at":"2017-08-14T16:11:31.055Z","bug_reporter_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2017-08-12T06:21:42.922Z","team_member_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2017-08-14T16:11:30.982Z","comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"The Birthdate Field on the KhanAcademy's [Sign Up](https://www.khanacademy.org/signup) page for new users has the year range from 2017 to 1897. \n{F210177}\nHowever, while signing up for a new account, I was able to set the year to 1033 by manipulating the data being sent to the server and the account was successfully created. I can also confirm the year by checking the settings page of my account. Please refer to the screenshots for information.\n{F210178}\n{F210179}\n{F210180}\n{F210181}\n\nI was also able to create a Child account with the same bug. Attaching the screenshot where the system says \"You don't have an email address connected to this Khan Academy account. Since you're **_1017 years old_**, you can connect an email address to your account, which will unlink it from your parent's account.\".\n{F210182}\n{F210183}\n\nSuggestion: Proper validation should be implemented on Birthdate field so that the user is not able to set any year other than what is being displayed on the dropdown.","weakness":{"id":57,"name":"Violation of Secure Design Principles"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[{"id":210177,"file_name":"01-daterange.png","expiring_url":"https://hackerone-us-west-2-production-attachments.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/000/210/177/efea550a8cddb95cd2dfc20026efe422f714622d/01-daterange.png?response-content-disposition=attachment%3B%20filename%3D%2201-daterange.png%22%3B%20filename%2A%3DUTF-8%27%2701-daterange.png\u0026response-content-type=image%2Fpng\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\u0026X-Amz-Credential=ASIAQGK6FURQREBPJLSS%2F20260429%2Fus-west-2%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\u0026X-Amz-Date=20260429T1017